  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN193.1-kilavi">poruḷvalitta neñciṟkuc collit talaimakaṉ celavaḻuṅkiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How HE prevented going by speaking to [his] heart that coveted wealth.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN193.1">
        <l>kāṉuyar maruṅkiṟ kavalai yallatu</l>
        <l>vāṉam vēṇṭā villē ruḻavar</l>
        <l>perunāḷ vēṭṭaṅ kiḷaiyeḻa vāytta</l>
        <l>porukaḷat toḻinta kurutic cevvāyp</l>
        <l>poṟitta pōlum vāṉiṟa verutti</l>
        <l>ṉaṇinta pōluñ ceñ<supplied>cevi</supplied> yeruvai</l>
        <l>poṟaiyaṭain teḻunta neṭuntāḷ <supplied>yā</supplied>at</l>
        <l>taruṅkavaṭ ṭuya<supplied>r</supplied>ciṉaip piḷḷai yūṭṭa</l>
        <l>viraintuvāy vaḻukkiya koḻuṅka ṇūṉṟaṭi</l>
        <l>tolpaci mutunari valci yāruñ</l>
        <l>curaṉamak keḷiya maṉṉē naṉmaṉaip</l>
        <l>paṉmāṇ ṭaṅkiya cāya liṉmoḻi</l>
        <l>muruntēr muṟuva liḷaiyōḷ</l>
        <l><supplied>pe</supplied>runtō ḷiṉṟuyil kaiviṭu kalaṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Easy for us indeed are the deserts, (11a-c)</l>
        <l>where the old jackal with ancient hunger becomes full on the food (10)</l>
        <l>of meat pieces with eyes of fat that slipped in haste from the beaks (9)</l>
        <l>of Brahminy kites with ears so red that they seem to be decorated (6)</l>
        <l>[and] necks of a colour so white that they seem to be imprinted(?), (5)</l>
        <l>[their] beaks red with the blood that stayed behind on the battlefield (4)</l>
        <l>that was attained when (3d)</l>
        <l>the ploughmen with bows as ploughs who do not need the sky, (2)</l>
        <l>but only the crossroads on the high sides of the forest, (1)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">rose with [their] kin for the great daily hunt, (3a-c)</l>
        <l>so as to feed [its] young ones in the high branches with difficult forks (8)</l>
        <l>of the long-trunked Yāam tree that rose close to the hillock. (7)</l>
        <l>[But] I won’t let go of the sweet sleep on the wide shoulders (14)</l>
        <l>of the young one with a smile [in which her teeth] resemble sprouts, (13)</l>
        <l>with graceful sweet words, who has [already] many times stayed [alone] (12)</l>
        <l rend="indent10">in the good house. (11d)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
